>how does one create oc
generally one begins with a concept either in response to a setting or personal desire. For many, an OC is a reflection of and vehicle for a fetish or mental trouble. For others, an OC is just another person in a world of fiction they enjoy (i.e. what the horsefuckers have been doing the last decade, mostly, and the harry potter people before then).
Once you have your base concept down, you settle on species, sex, general personality, and so on. This can extend to making satellite characters you don't put as much effort into to give them a family, or you can eschew that and just have them adrift in the universe. After that, you start getting into the granular bits: coloration, physical attributes and skills (or lack thereof), personal likes and dislikes, and so on until you get to (in my opinion) the hardest part: the name. Names take me forever to nail down.
